 conference]] tradition and contain a modest number of papers and are published several years after the conference.\n\n===Funding Sources===\nIWOTA has received support from many sources, including the [[National Science Foundation]]<ref name=\"NSF0126746\" /><ref name=\"NSF0536873\" /><ref>{{cite web | title = Travel Support for IWOTA 2004 | url = https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=0422952&HistoricalAwards=false}}</ref>\n<ref name = \"NSF0757364\">{{cite web | title = NSF Award | series=Nineteenth International Workshop on Operator Theory and Applications | place = Williamsburg, Virginia | year=2008 | publisher = [[National Science Foundation]] | url = https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=0757364&HistoricalAwards=false}}</ref>\n,<ref>{{cite web | title = Travel Support for IWOTA 2009 | url = https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=0902270&HistoricalAwards=false}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Travel Support for IWOTA 2012 | url = https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=1240475&HistoricalAwards=false}}</ref> the [[London Mathematical Society]],<ref name = \"newcastle\">{{Cite web | title = IWOTA 2004 | url = http://conferences.ncl.ac.uk/iwota/ | website = www.ncl.ac.uk | accessdate = 2015-11-24}}</ref> the [[Engineering and Physical Sciences Research Council]],<ref name = \"newcastle\" /> [[Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft]],<ref>{{Cite web|title = IWOTA 2010|url = http://www3.math.tu-berlin.de/numerik/iwota_2010/|website = www3.math.tu-berlin.de|accessdate = 2015-11-22}}</ref> Secretar\u00eda de Estado de Investigaci\u00f3n, Desarrollo e Innovaci\u00f3n (Spain),<ref>{{Cite web | title = IWOTA 2011|url = http://congreso.us.es/iwota2011/ | website = www.us.es | accessdate = 2015-11-24}}</ref> [[Australian Mathematical Sciences Institute]],<ref>{{cite web | title = AMSI Annual Report 2012-2013 | url = http://amsi.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/AMSI_annual_report2012-13.pdf | page = 24}}</ref> [[National Board for Higher Mathematics]],<ref name = \"india\">{{Cite web | title = IWOTA 2013 | url = http://math.iisc.ernet.in/~iwota2013/ | website = www.iisc.ernet.in | accessdate = 2015-11-24}}</ref> [[International Centre for Theoretical Physics]],<ref name = \"southafrica\">{{cite book | editor-last = Grobler | editor-first = J.J. | editor2-last = Labuschagne | editor2-first = L.E. | editor3-last = M\u00f6ller | editor3-first = M. | title = Operator Algebras, Operator Theory and Applications | series = Operator Theory: Advances and Applications | volume = 195 | edition = 1 | publisher = [[Birkh\u00e4user | Birkh\u00e4user Verlag]] | location = Basel | page = vii | date = 2010 | doi = 10.1007/978-3-0346-0174-0 | isbn = 978-3-0346-0173-3 | issn = 0255-0156 | url = https://www.springer.com/us/book/9783034601733}}</ref> [[Indian Statistical Institute]],<ref name=\"image\" /> [[Korea Research Foundation]],<ref>{{cite book | editor-last = Ando | editor-first = T. | editor2-last = Curto | editor2-first = R.E. | editor3-last = Jung | editor3-first = I.B. |display-editors = 3 | editor4-last = Lee | editor4-first = W.Y. | title = Recent Advances in Operator Theory and Applications | series = Operator Theory: Advances and Applications | volume = 187 | edition = 1 | publisher = [[Birkh\u00e4user | Birkh\u00e4user Verlag]] | location = Basel | page = viii | date = 2009 | doi = 10.1007/978-3-7643-8893-5 | isbn = 978-3-7643-8892-8 | issn = 0255-0156 | url = https://www.springer.com/us/book/9783764388928}}</ref> [[United States-India Science & Technology Endowment Fund]],<ref name = \"india\" /> [[Nederlandse Organisatie voor Wetenschappelijk Onderzoek]],<ref name=\"netherlands\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.math.vu.nl/~ran/iwota2014/|title=IWOTA 2014|website=www.math.vu.nl|accessdate=2015-11-22}}</ref> the Commission for Developing Countries of the [[International Mathematical Union]],<ref name = \"program\" /><ref name = \"southafrica\" /> Stichting Advancement of Mathematics (Netherlands),<ref name = \"program\" /> the [[National Research Foundation of South Africa]],<ref name = \"southafrica\" /> and [[Birkh\u00e4user | Birkh\u00e4user Publishing Ltd]].\n\n==The IWOTA Steering Committee==\nIWOTA is directed by a steering committee<ref>{{cite web | title = International Workshop on Operator Theory and its Applications (IWOTA)| url = http://math.wustl.edu/~iwota}}</ref> which chooses the site for the next meeting, elects the chief local organizer(s) and insures the appearance of the enduring themes of IWOTA. The sub-themes of an IWOTA workshop and the lecturers are chosen by the local organizing committee after hearing the steering committee's board. The board consists of its vice presidents: Joseph A. Ball, J. William Helton (Chair), M. A. Kaashoek, Igor Klep, [[Christiane Tretter]], Victor Vinnikov and Hugo J. Woerdeman. In addition, past chief organizers who remain active in IWOTA are members of the steering committee. The board governs IWOTA with consultation and the consent of the full steering committee. Honorary members of the steering committee, elected in 2016, are: Israel Gohberg (deceased), Leiba Rodman (deceased), Tsuyoshi Ando, Harry Dym,  Ciprian Foia\u015f (deceased), Heinz Langer, Nikolai Nikolski.\n\n==Future IWOTA Meetings==\n* IWOTA 2020 will be held at [[Lancaster University]] in [[Lancaster, Lancashire|Lancaster]], [[United Kingdom]]. Main organizer is Gordon Blower. Dates are August 17\u201321, 2020\n* IWOTA 2021 will be held at [[Chapman University]] in [[Orange, California]], [[United States]]. Main organizers are Daniel Alpay and Mihaela Vajiac. Dates are August 9-13, 2021\n* IWOTA 2022 will be held at [[Agricultural University of Krak\u00f3w]], [[Jagiellonian University]] and [[AGH University of Science and Technology]] in [[Krak\u00f3w]], [[Poland]]. Main organizers are Marek Ptak and Micha\u0142 Wojtylak. Dates are September 6-10, 2022\n\n==Israel Gohberg ILAS-IWOTA Lecture==\n\nThe Israel Gohberg ILAS-IWOTA Lecture was introduced in August 2016 and honors the legacy of Israel Gohberg, whose research crossed borders between operator theory, linear algebra, and related fields. This lecture is in collaboration with the [[International Linear Algebra Society]] (ILAS).<ref>{{cite web | title = International Linear Algebra Society (ILAS)| url = http://www.ilasic.org}}</ref> This series of lectures will be delivered at IWOTA and ILAS Conferences, in different years, in the approximate ratio two-thirds at IWOTA and one-third at ILAS. The first three lectures will take place at IWOTA 2020, ILAS 2022, and IWOTA 2024. Donations for the Israel Gohberg ILAS-IWOTA Lecture Fund are most welcome and can be submitted via the ILAS donation form.<ref>{{cite web | title = International Linear Algebra Society (ILAS) donation form | url = http://ilasic.org/misc/donationform.html}}</ref> Donations are tax deductible in the United States.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.springer.com/series/4850 Operator Theory: Advances and Applications Series on Springer website]\n* [http://www.math.u-bordeaux.fr/~iwota/ IWOTA 2000 - Bordeaux, France]\n* [http://www.math.snu.ac.kr/workshop/iwota2006/ IWOTA 2006 - Seoul, Korea]\n* [http://www.puk.ac.za/fakulteite/natuur/bwi-nav/iwota/ IWOTA 2007 - Potchefstroom, South Africa]\n* [http://www.math.wm.edu/~vladi/IWOTA/IWOTA2008.htm IWOTA 2008 - Williamsburg, Virginia, U.S.A]\n* [https://www3.math.tu-berlin.de/numerik/iwota_2010/ IWOTA 2010 - Berlin, Germany]\n* [http://congreso.us.es/iwota2011/ IWOTA 2011 - Seville, Spain]\n* [http://conferences.science.unsw.edu.au/IWOTA2012/ IWOTA 2012 - Sydney, Australia]\n* [http://math.iisc.ernet.in/~iwota2013/ IWOTA 2013 - Bangalore, India]\n* [http://www.math.vu.nl/~ran/iwota2014/ IWOTA 2014 - Amsterdam, Netherlands]\n* [http://www.gmu.ge/iwota2015/ IWOTA 2015 - Tbilisi, Georgia]\n* [http://openscholarship.wustl.edu/iwota2016/ IWOTA 2016 - St. Louis, Missouri, USA]\n* [https://www.tu-chemnitz.de/mathematik/iwota2017/ IWOTA 2017 - Chemnitz, Germany]\n* [https://iwota2019.math.tecnico.ulisboa.pt/home IWOTA 2019 - Lisbon, Portugal]\n* [https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/maths/iwota2020/ IWOTA 2020 - Lancaster, United Kingdom]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:International Workshop on Operator Theory and its Applications (IWOTA)}}\n[[Category:Mathematics conferences]]\n[[Category:Operator theory]]\n[[Category:Functional analysis]]\n[[Category:Mathematical analysis]]\n", "text_old": "'''International Workshop on Operator Theory and its Applications (IWOTA)''' was started in 1981<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news | author = J. W. Helton | title = A conference report | journal = Integral Equations and Operator Theory | volume = 5 | year = 1982 | pages = 605\u2013607 | url=https://link.springer.com/journal/20/5/1/page/2#page-1 }}</ref>  to bring together [[mathematician]]s and [[engineer]]s working in [[operator theory|operator theoretic]] side of [[functional analysis]] and its applications to related fields.<ref name=\"NSF0126746\">{{cite web | title=NSF Award | series=13th International Workshop on Operator Theory and Applications | place=Blacksburg, Virginia | year=2002 | publisher = [[National Science Foundation]] | url = https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=0126746&HistoricalAwards=false}}</ref><ref name=\"NSF0536873\">{{cite web | title=NSF Award | series=IWOTA 2005 - International Workshop on Operator Theory and Applications | place=Storrs, CT | year=2005 | publisher = [[National Science Foundation]] | url = https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=0536873&HistoricalAwards=false}}</ref>  These include:\n\n* [[Differential equations]] and [[Integral equations]]\n* [[Complex analysis]] and [[Harmonic analysis]]\n* [[Linear system]] and [[Control theory]]\n* [[Mathematical physics]]\n* [[Signal processing]]\n* [[Numerical analysis]]\n\nThe other major branch of [[operator theory]], [[Operator algebras]] (C* and von Neumann Algebras), is not heavily represented at IWOTA and has its own conferences.\n\nIWOTA gathers leading experts from all over the world for an intense exchange of new results, information and opinions, and for tracing the future developments in the field.  The IWOTA meetings provide opportunities for participants (including young [[research]]ers) to present their own work in invited and contributed talks, to interact with other [[research]]ers from around the globe, and to broaden their knowledge of the field.<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://www.ams.org/notices/201501/rnoti-p74.pdf#page=4 | title = Notices of the American Mathematical Society | series = Vol. 62, No. 1 | date = 2015 | page = 4 | publisher = [[American Mathematical Society]] }}</ref> \nIn addition, IWOTA emphasizes cross-disciplinary interaction among [[mathematician]]s, [[Electrical engineering|electrical engineers]] and [[Mathematical physics|mathematical physicists]]. In the even years, the IWOTA workshop is a satellite meeting to the biennial International Symposium on the Mathematical Theory of Networks and Systems (MTNS).<ref name=\"mtns\">{{cite book |editor1=Levan, N. | title=International Symposium on Mathematical Theory of Networks and Systems : August 5-7, 1981, Miramar-Sheraton Hotel, Santa Monica, California | publisher=Western Periodicals Co | location=North Hollywood, California | year=1981 | page=iii | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_rJQAAAAYAAJ }}</ref> From the humble beginnings in the early 80's,<ref name=\":0\" /> the IWOTA workshops grew to become one of the largest continuing conferences attended by the community of researchers in [[operator theory]].<ref name=\"image\">{{Cite web|url = http://www.ilasic.org/IMAGE/IMAGES/image52.pdf#page=35|title = IMAGE, the Bulletin of the International Linear Algebra Society | date=2014| page=35 | publisher=International Linear Algebra Society }}</ref>\n\n==History of IWOTA==\n\n===First IWOTA Meeting===\nThe International Workshop on Operator Theory and its Applications was started on August 1, 1981,<ref name=\":0\" /> adjacent to the International Symposium on Mathematical Theory of Networks and Systems (MTNS)<ref name=\"mtns\" /> with goal of exposing [[operator theory|operator theorists,]] even [[Pure mathematics|pure]] theorists, to recent developments in [[engineering]] (especially ''[[H-infinity methods in control theory]]'') which had a significant intersection with [[operator theory]]. [[Israel Gohberg]] was the visionary and driving force of IWOTA<ref>{{cite book |last=Langer |first=Heinz |editor1 = Bart, Harm | editor2 = Hempfling, Thomas | editor3 = Kaashoek, Marinus A. | title = Israel Gohberg and Friends: On the Occasion of his 80th Birthday|pages=249\u2013252 |chapter=VI.2. The Vienna University of Technology at Vienna, Austria | publisher = [[Birkh\u00e4user | Birkh\u00e4user Verlag]]| location = Basel| isbn = 9783764387334 | chapter-url=https://www.springer.com/us/book/9783764387334 |date=2008-06-23 }}</ref> and president of the IWOTA Steering Committee. From the beginning, J. W. Helton and M. A. Kaashoek served as vice presidents of the steering committee.\n\n===West Meets East===\nBesides the excitement of mathematical discovery over the decades at IWOTA, there was great excitement when the [[Iron Curtain|curtain]] between [[Eastern bloc|Soviet bloc]] and Western operator theorists fell. Until 1990, these two collections of extremely strong mathematicians seldom met due to the tight [[Human rights in the Soviet Union#Freedom of movement|restrictions on travel]] from and in the [[Communist state|communist countries]]. When the [[Iron Curtain|curtain]] dropped, the western mathematicians knew the classic Soviet papers but had a spotty knowledge of much of what else their counterparts were doing.<ref>{{cite book |last=Landau |first=Henry J. |editor1 = Bart, Harm | editor2 = Hempfling, Thomas | editor3 = Kaashoek, Marinus A. | title = Israel Gohberg and Friends: On the Occasion of his 80th Birthday|pages=309\u2013310 |chapter=To Israel |   publisher = [[Birkh\u00e4user | Birkh\u00e4user Verlag]]| location = Basel| isbn = 9783764387334 | chapter-url=https://www.springer.com/us/book/9783764387334 |date=2008-06-23 }}</ref> [[Israel Gohberg|Gohberg]] was one of the operator theorists who knew both sides and he guided IWOTA, a western institution, in bringing (and funding) many prominent [[Post-Soviet states|FSU bloc]] operator theorists to speak at the meetings. As the IWOTA programs demonstrate,<ref name = \"program\">{{Cite web | url=http://www.gmu.ge/iwota2015/Files/Program_IWOTA_2015.pdf | title=IWOTA-2015 Program | date=2015 | publisher=Georgian Mathematical Union, [[Georgian National Academy of Sciences]] }}</ref> this significantly accelerated the cultures' mutual assimilation.<ref>\n{{cite book | editor-last = Dijksma | editor-first = A. | editor2-last = Kaashoek | editor2-first = M.A. | editor3-last = Ran | editor3-first = A.C.M. | title = Recent Advances in Operator Theory | series = Operator Theory: Advances and Applications | volume = 124 | edition = 1 | publisher = [[Birkh\u00e4user | Birkh\u00e4user Verlag]] | location = Basel, Boston, Berlin | pages = xiii\u2013xxii | date = 2001 |isbn = 978-3-0348-9516-3  | issn = 0255-0156 | url=https://books.google.com/?id=Rb4fnwEACAAJ&dq=isbn+9783034895163}}\n</ref>\n\n===Previous IWOTA Meetings===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! #\n! Year \n! Location \n! Chief Organizer(s) \n! Proceedings in OTAA-series<ref name=\"OTAA\">{{cite book | editor-last = Ball | editor-first = J.A. | editor2-last = Dym | editor2-first = H. | editor3-last = Kaashoek | editor3-first = M.A.  | editor4-last = Langer | editor4-first = H. | editor5-last = Tretter| editor5-first = C.|editor5-link= Christiane Tretter | title = Operator Theory: Advances and Applications| series = Series| publisher = [[Birkh\u00e4user | Birkh\u00e4user Verlag]]| location = Basel| issn = 0255-0156| url = https://www.springer.com/series/4850?detailsPage=titles/}}</ref>\n! Participation\n|-\n| 1\t\n| 1981\n| {{flag